  <title>Fun with ViewState</title>
  <description />
  <content>&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
I read Dave Reed&amp;#39;sblog posting on &amp;quot;Truly Understanding ViewState&amp;quot;:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
&lt;a href="http://weblogs.asp.net/infinitiesloop/archive/2006/08/03/Truly-Understanding-Viewstate.aspx"&gt;http://weblogs.asp.net/infinitiesloop/archive/2006/08/03/Truly-Understanding-Viewstate.aspx&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
I can&amp;#39;t say I didn&amp;#39;t not dis-believe what he said, after all he DOES work for Microsoft.&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;But I wanted to see examples of when &lt;a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms972976.aspx"&gt;ViewState&lt;/a&gt;tracking took action and when it did not.&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;If you want an in-depth understanding, read his post.&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;But below is what I think is the most important point I take from his post that is vital to understanding &lt;a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms972976.aspx"&gt;ViewState&lt;/a&gt;,thereby understanding how to best lighten the load of your post-backs, thereby optimizing the performance of your web application.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline"&gt;The biggest misconception about ViewState:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style="margin-left: 0.375in; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in"&gt;
	&lt;li style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; vertical-align: middle"&gt;&lt;a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms972976.aspx"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;ViewState&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt; (or more specifically &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style: italic; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;ViewState	tracking&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;) is	simply how all ASP.NET Web Controls maintain their values.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 0in 0.375in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;
&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
This leads to someincorrect assumptions:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style="margin-left: 0.375in; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in"&gt;
	&lt;li style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; vertical-align: middle"&gt;&lt;a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms972976.aspx"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;ViewState&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt; is proportional to the	number of controls on the page&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul style="margin-left: 0.375in; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in"&gt;
	&lt;li style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; vertical-align: middle"&gt;&lt;a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms972976.aspx"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;ViewState&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt; is tracking all the values	on those controls in EVERY post-back so that it can re-populate ALL of	those values&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline"&gt;The most important thing to understand aboutViewState:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style="margin-left: 0.375in; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in"&gt;
	&lt;li style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; vertical-align: middle"&gt;&lt;a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms972976.aspx"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;ViewState&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt; is used by controls to store	ALL of their dynamic properties, but &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms972976.aspx"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;ViewState&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt; TRACKING is only used to	track changes to those properties after &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms972976.aspx"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;ViewState&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt; Tracking is turned on.&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;In ASP.NET, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms972976.aspx"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;ViewState&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt; tracking is turned on after	the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style: italic; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;On_Init&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt"&gt;	event of web controls themselves (NOT the page).&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Knowing when it matters goes a long way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
Enough talk.&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Following are several examples that illustrate what I mean, half of which may be surprising if you don&amp;#39;t read &lt;a href="http://weblogs.asp.net/infinitiesloop/archive/2006/08/03/Truly-Understanding-Viewstate.aspx"&gt;Dave&amp;#39;spost&lt;/a&gt;.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0in"&gt;
&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/p&gt;
